Global Funds Sell Net 6.75 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-05-04T03:30:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/global-funds-sell-net-6-75-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 6.75
billion rupees ($152 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, climbed 4.6 percent to 908.4 billion rupees, or
36.6 percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 11.8 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on yesterday, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
